    "description": "Ohashi Technica Inc., together with its subsidiaries, develops, manufactures, and sells automotive parts and other components in Japan, the United States, China, Thailand, ASEAN, Europe, Taiwan, and internationally. The company offers automotive parts comprising engine and mission, differential, brake, body and chasse, and interior/exterior components; and information technology (IT) and communications device parts, including mobile phone hinges and other parts. It also provides precision oil pump shafts used in dual clutch transmission; and piezo injector components for diesel engines. In addition, the company plans, develops, produces, and markets precision components assembled to various products in automobile and other industries, as well as engages in procurement, export, and logistics businesses. It serves auto and auto part unit equipment manufacturers. The company was formerly known as Ohashi Shoji, Inc. and changed its name to Ohashi Technica Inc. in May 1987. Ohashi Technica Inc. was founded in 1951 and is headquartered in Minato, Japan."
